Childhood socioeconomic position

1 Description of DataSchema variable

The description of harmonised variable is the following:

  • Short name: childsep
  • Variable label: Childhood socioeconomic position
  • Variable description: Childhood socioeconomic position
  • Domain: Socio-demographic and economic characteristics
  • Value type: Categorical
  • Category coding:
Code Category Label
0 High
1 Medium
2 Low
  • Category missings:
Code Category Label
991 CAPI/interviewer error

993 Disable to measure
994 Not attempt/not done
995 Does not answer
996 Not applicable
997 Refuse
998 Do not know
999 Missing

2.1.1.2 Harmonisation algorithm

To compute childsep from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • 1,5:8 into 1
  • 2:4 into 0
  • 9:12,14:15 into 2
  • -9 into 997
  • -8 into 998
  • -1 into 996
  • 13 into 999

R script:

ELSA_ds_w1 <- ELSA_w1 %>%
  mutate(childsep = case_when(
    difjob %in% c(2:4) ~ 0,
    difjob %in% c(1,5:8) ~ 1,
    difjob %in% c(9:12,14:15) ~ 2,
    difjob %in% c(-9) ~ 997,
    difjob %in% c(-8) ~ 998,
    difjob %in% c(-1) ~ 996,
    difjob %in% c(13) ~ 999,
    TRUE ~ 999
  )) %>%
  select(id, childsep)

ELSA_ds <- ELSA_ds_w1 %>%
  mutate(misscode = case_when(
    childsep %in% c(991:999) ~ 1,
    TRUE ~ 0
  ))

2.1.2.2 Harmonisation algorithm

To compute childsep from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • keep childsep from wave 1
  • 1,5:8 into 1
  • 2:4 into 0
  • 9:12,14:15 into 2
  • -9 into 997
  • -8 into 998
  • -1 into 996
  • 13 into 999

R script:

ELSA_ds_w2 <- ELSA_w2 %>%
  left_join(ELSA_ds, by = "id") %>%
  mutate(childsep.w2 = case_when(
    !childsep %in% c(991:999) & !is.na(childsep) ~ childsep,
    DiFJob %in% c(2:4) ~ 0,
    DiFJob %in% c(1,5:8) ~ 1,
    DiFJob %in% c(9:12,14:15) ~ 2,
    DiFJob %in% c(-9) ~ 997,
    DiFJob %in% c(-8) ~ 998,
    DiFJob %in% c(-1,-2) & !is.na(childsep) ~ childsep,
    DiFJob %in% c(-1,-2) & is.na(childsep) ~ 996,
    DiFJob %in% c(13) ~ 999,
    TRUE ~ 999
  )) %>%
  select(id, childsep = childsep.w2)

ELSA_ds <- ELSA_ds %>%
  full_join(ELSA_ds_w2 %>%
              mutate(misscode = case_when(
                childsep %in% c(991:999) ~ 1,
                TRUE ~ 0
              )), by = "id", suffix = c(".pw",".w2")) %>%
  mutate(childsep = case_when(
    !is.na(misscode.w2) ~ childsep.w2,
    is.na(misscode.w2) ~ childsep.pw
  )) %>%
  mutate(misscode = case_when(
    childsep %in% c(991:999) ~ 1,
    TRUE ~ 0
  )) %>%
  select(id, childsep, misscode)

2.1.3.2 Harmonisation algorithm

To compute childsep from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • keep childsep from previous waves
  • 1,5:8 into 1
  • 2:4 into 0
  • 9:12,14:15 into 2
  • -9 into 997
  • -8 into 998
  • -1,-2 into 996
  • 13 into 999

R script:

ELSA_ds_w3 <- ELSA_w3 %>%
  left_join(ELSA_ds, by = "id") %>%
  mutate(childsep.w3 = case_when(
    !childsep %in% c(991:999) & !is.na(childsep) ~ childsep,
    difjob %in% c(2:4) ~ 0,
    difjob %in% c(1,5:8) ~ 1,
    difjob %in% c(9:12,14:15) ~ 2,
    difjob %in% c(-9) ~ 997,
    difjob %in% c(-8) ~ 998,
    difjob %in% c(-1,-2) & !is.na(childsep) ~ childsep,
    difjob %in% c(-1,-2) & is.na(childsep) ~ 996,
    difjob %in% c(13) ~ 999,
    TRUE ~ 999
  )) %>%
  select(id, childsep = childsep.w3)

ELSA_ds <- ELSA_ds %>%
  full_join(ELSA_ds_w3 %>%
              mutate(misscode = case_when(
                childsep %in% c(991:999) ~ 1,
                TRUE ~ 0
              )), by = "id", suffix = c(".pw",".w3")) %>%
  mutate(childsep = case_when(
    !is.na(misscode.w3) ~ childsep.w3,
    is.na(misscode.w3) ~ childsep.pw
  )) %>%
  mutate(misscode = case_when(
    childsep %in% c(991:999) ~ 1,
    TRUE ~ 0
  )) %>%
  select(id, childsep, misscode)
